Syntax: CHECKBOX <ON> #line @column 'text-for-selection' 
      <COLOR=color> <SUBSTITUTE='text-for-substitution'>; 

Defines choices that a user can make within a dialog box.

Syntax: MENU menu-bar;  
  MENU pull-down-menu;  

where:

menu-bar names the catalog entry that stores the menus.

pull-down-menu names the menu that appears when the user selects an item in the menu bar.

This statement names the catalog entry that stores the menus or defines a menu.

Syntax: ITEM command <option(s)><action-options>;  
         ITEM 'menu-item' <option(s)><action-options>;  

Identifies an item to be listed in a menu bar or in a menu.
